 :tx/rationale "METABOLIC-FOUNDATION: The store needs a metabolism — continuous, autonomous semantic computation at write time. Currently the store is passive (datoms go in, nothing comes out unless agent asks). Every process obligation (observe, harvest, reconcile, audit) is a ceremony the agent must remember, and ceremonies decay under pressure. The radical insight: make transact() self-aware. After committing datoms, the store examines what happened and annotates the transaction entity with derived metadata. This inverts the information architecture from 'agent observes world → agent writes datoms → store stores them' to 'agent writes datoms → store stores them → store observes what happened → store writes metadata'. The store becomes its own first observer. This is the store comonad principle from Session 029 made literal. ALGEBRAIC: Transaction digests are morphism annotations — metadata about the arrows in the category (Store, transact). They form a natural transformation from the raw-store functor to the annotated-store functor, enriching every morphism with semantic metadata while preserving categorical structure (composition, identity, merge as coproduct). ARCHITECTURAL PRINCIPLE: Move semantic computation from query time to write time. The store already maintains EAVT/AEVT/VAET/AVET structural indexes at write time. Metabolic transactions extend this to semantic indexes (coherence, novelty, cross-references) at write time. COST: ~5 extra datoms per transaction (~40% growth). At 31k datoms and ~100 tx/session, this is negligible for years. TRACES TO: SEED.md §4 (datom abstraction), SEED.md §7 (self-improvement loop), INV-STORE-014 (every store interaction is an observation)."
